# Autonomy Level

## Current Mode: SUPERVISED

The delivery agent generates all outputs automatically. Write actions (posting comments, sending messages, updating tickets) require your explicit approval before execution.

## Autonomy Levels

| Level | Reports | Write Actions |
|-------|---------|---------------|
| **human-in-the-loop** | Manual trigger, manual review | Blocked |
| **supervised** (default) | Auto-generated | You approve each one |
| **autonomous** | Auto-generated | Auto-executed |

## Confidence Thresholds

| Level | Criteria | Behavior |
|-------|----------|----------|
| **High** | >90% required data available | Proceed normally |
| **Medium** | 70-90% data available | Proceed with "Medium confidence" caveat |
| **Low** | <70% data available | Block write actions, suggest manual verification |

## Tool Risk Classification

**Safe (auto-approvable)**: Read operations — searching tickets, querying data, fetching pages.

**Gated (require approval)**: Write operations — posting comments, sending messages, transitioning tickets, creating tickets.

When in doubt, show the output and wait for approval. Never execute a write action silently.
